http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 6 Mar 2017
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2017; 30(10) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=23121


Rabies, Hungary
---------------
Information received on and dated [6 Mar 2017] from Dr Lajos Bognar, deputy state secretary chief veterinary officer, Food Chain Safety Department, Ministry of Agriculture, Budapest, Hungary

Summary
Report type: immediate notification (final report)
Start date: 27 Feb 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 3 Mar 2017
Date event resolved: 3 Mar 2017
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 15 Feb 2016
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: rabies virus
Serotype: RABV
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic and advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Bekecs, Borsod-Abauj-Zemplen
Date of start of the outbreak: 27 Feb 2017
Outbreak status: resolved on 3 Mar 2017
Epidemiological unit: village
Total animals affected: species / susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
Red fox _Vulpes vulpes_ (Canidae) / - / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreaks(s): contact with wild species
Epidemiological comments: the area of finding is inside the area to be orally vaccinated during the next spring campaign between [1 and 12 Apr 2017].

Control measures
Measures applied: disinfection/disinfestations, official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists), no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Food Chain Safety Office (NFCSO), Animal Health Directorate (AHDD) (National laboratory) / Red Fox / histopathological examination / 3 Mar 2017 / negative
National Food Chain Safety Office (NFCSO), Animal Health Directorate (AHDD) (National laboratory) / Red Fox / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 3 Mar 2017 / negative

Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Hungary was close to eliminating rabies. The last reported case was in 2010. Oral rabies vaccination of red foxes (_Vulpes vulpes_) has been successful, but this episode alerts that campaigns should be continued and perhaps improved. - Mod.PMB

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4893209,112.]
